This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a supervised feature learning approach for image classification using deep convolutional neural networks. It also mentions achieving state-of-the-art performances on several public benchmarks for action and object category recognition, which are common tasks in computer vision. Other likely sub-categories include Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Multimedia (cs.MM) as these fields are closely related to computer vision and deep learning.
